org.omancode.r.types

Class RVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.omancode.r.types.RVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CBuilder

    public class RVector
extends Object
implements CBuilder
    Represents a vector of a single Java type. All elements of the vector must be of this type. Provides methods to convert to/from an REXPVector for use with R.
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

        Parameters:
        name - vector name
        rexp - source of vector values
        Throws:
        UnsupportedTypeException - if rexp is of an unsupported type (ie: no corresponding primitive list implementation exists)

        RFaceException - if problem determining dimnames attribute.
